Types of Data Collected
​
Personal Data
While using our Service, we do not request any personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you (“Personal Data”) directly. However we may ask you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information when you decide to send us your feedback or bug report. Personally identifiable information may include, but is not limited to: email address, first name and last name, app version and language.
​
Usage Data
When you access the Service through a mobile device, we may collect certain information automatically, including, but not limited to, the type of mobile device you use, your mobile device unique ID, the IP address of your mobile device, your mobile operating system, the type of mobile Internet browser you use, your geographic position, unique device identifiers and other diagnostic data (“Usage Data”).
Log Data
We want to inform you that whenever you use our Service, in a case of an error in the app we collect data and information (through third party products) on your phone called Log Data. This Log Data may include information such as your device Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, device name, operating system version, the configuration of the app when utilizing our Service, the time and date of your use of the Service, and other statistics.
​
Tracking & Cookies Data
We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track the activity on our Service and hold certain information. Cookies are files with small amount of data which may include an anonymous unique identifier. Cookies are sent to your browser from a website and stored on your device. Tracking technologies also used are beacons, tags, and scripts to collect and track information and to improve and analyze our Service.
​
What do we do with the data we collect?
​
The information that we collect is required in order for us to better understand your needs and provide you with better service, and in particular for the following reasons: in-app experience, in order to improve our products and services, we need some information.
We are dedicated to keeping your personal information safe. We take all the necessary actions to prevent unauthorized access to protect the information we collect from our users.
​
Cookies
​
“Cookies” are files with a small amount of data that are commonly used as anonymous unique identifiers. These are sent to your browser from the websites that you visit and are stored on your device’s internal memory. It helps the website to remember information about your visit and allows the website to respond to you as an individual. The application can tailor its operations to your needs by collecting and remembering information about your preferences. This Service does not use these “cookies” explicitly. However, the Application may use third-party code and libraries that use “cookies” to collect information and improve their services. If this is the case, data is immediately removed from the system after it is used to improve the service provided. A cookie does not give us access to your device or any personal information about you, except those you choose to share with us. You always have the ability and right to accept or decline cookies. Please keep in mind that most web browsers directly accept cookies and you may need to modify your browser settings in order to decline the acception of these cookies.
​
Security
​
We value your trust in the provision of your personal information and we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect it. We do not store your personal data or transfer it to other third parties. You can limit the collection or use of personal information by disallowing access to personal information in the application’s authorization permission dialog box. You can also go to settings and revoke the app’s permissions to access the data.
​
Links to other websites
​
Our Application may include links to other websites. However, once you’ve used these links to leave our Application, you should be aware that we have no control over the content you find elsewhere. As a result, we cannot guarantee the security or privacy of any information you provide while visiting such sites, and these sites are not covered by this privacy statement. You should proceed with caution and carefully read the privacy statement for the website in question.
